records.addlTxt:
Defendant Luis Roberto Rodriguez in court with attorney Jamie Francis Cimpl-Wiemer.  Joanne L Hardtke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Sentencing proceeds.  Statements made by the State and defense counsel.

AS TO COUNT 1:   Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 36 MONTHS.  
INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 18 MONTHS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 18 MONTHS. 
Credit given for ZERO days time served if revoked.

Court finds defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
Court finds defendant is NOT eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.

COURT STAYS sentence and places defendant on PROBATION for 3 YEARS under the supervision of the Wisconsin Department of Corrections.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION (AS TO COUNT 1): 
* Comply with the standard rules of probation/extended supervision.
* SERVE 45 DAYS "condition time" at the House of Correction with release privileges for employment and treatment purposes only - STAYED until 06-15-2015 at 12:00 PM.  Court allows "GOOD TIME CREDIT" as to the condition time.
* No contact with the victim.
* Seek and maintain full-time employment,
* Complete a job training program to enhance ability to obtain employment.
* Complete an anger management class.
* Complete a cognitive behavior therapy class.
* Complete a parenting class.
* Cooperate and participate with an AODA assessment and follow any recommended treatment.
* Maintain absolute sobriety and submit to random urine screens.
* Provide a DNA sample and PAY DNA surcharge - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
* PAY the balance of all applicable court costs, fees, and surcharges - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
* PAY restitution in the amount of $34,417.19 payable to the Crime Victim Impact Compensation Fund - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

OTHER COURT ORDERS:
* Court will allow probation to be transferred to Chippewa County, if accepted.
* The conditions of extended supervision are the same as the conditions of probation.
* Court will grant a petition for expungment if the defendant successfully completes probation without any violations AND makes a good faith effort to pay a substantial amount towards restitution.
* Court will allow defendant to work in the inmate worker program, if deemed appropriate.
  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor.  
Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.
Appeal rights given.

Defendant Luis Roberto Rodriguez in court with attorney Jamie Francis Cimpl-Wiemer.  Joanne L Hardtke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

This matter was originally scheduled for a Jury Trial today, however, the parties have now reached an agreement.

AS TO COUNT 1:    Defendant changes plea to "NO CONTEST". Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Defendant is advised he is a convicted felon and may not possess any firearms. Defendant is advised he is unable to vote in any election until civil rights are restored. Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.
